			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is a test of patience:<BR>
<BR>
   Being a fellow shaman, i camped this bear for 7 days, with no spawn. There are two wandering icebone skellys, NOT LICH OR HIS PET, you must kill them first, and come back to the caves about 6 hrs later and wait. The two ib's will wander again. kill them again and wait, sometimes the bear will drop within 30mins after the ib's have been killed a second time. If not--- then wait, i camped him on a saturday morning from 8:30am to 10:30pm, yes, that's how long it took it to spawn.<BR>
my advice is, kill the wandering ib's, then go hunt something for 6hrs, and head back to the cave, and wait for the ib's, kill them, and wait for at least 40mins, every so often hit sense animal, best place to be in my opinion, is by the broken transporter room, that's where we got him---with the help of a lvl 52 Cavalier---(thx bro), and if no spawn, the kill the ib's again, and go hunt something for another 6hrs, come back to the caves, and wait, you maybe suprised, he dropped for me, big bear too. <BR>
<BR>
just my 2cc, :)<BR>
hope this info helps you brave shammys<BR>
Prexian Nomads
